      "content": "When the obvious causes—theft, bad paperwork, and simple misplacement—are ruled out, you move into more complex, almost systemic issues. One unconventional possibility is equipment malfunction, such as a scanner or automated picking system occasionally skipping a scan or misregistering a location. Another, less common, possibility is material degradation or damage so minor it's not logged as scrap, but it still removes it from the sellable inventory. You could also look into environmental factors, like dust or humidity affecting small components, though this is usually more relevant to quality than count.",
